<B><FONT SIZE=+2>Art Museum</FONT></B>

<P>-an experimental database system for an electronic gallery

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Data Model</FONT></B>

<P>-no image object
<BR>-only whole images
<BR>-implemented using conventional relational database

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Content-Based Similarity Retrieval</FONT></B><B></B>

<P>-retrival by sketch or example
<OL>
<LI>
<B>Adaptive Image Abstraction:</B>&nbsp; automatic creation of image abstraction</LI>

<LI>
<B>Flexible Pattern Matching:</B>&nbsp; rough sketch by the user is good
enough for retrieval.&nbsp; can use sketch, example, or compositions.</LI>
</OL>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>Similarity Measures and Ranking</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI>
global correlation</LI>

<LI>
deviation</LI>
</UL>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>Queryn by Subjective Descriptions</FONT></B>

<P>-capture user-specific subjective descriptions ascribed to images
<BR>-relate subjective keywords with the pictorial features

